      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on a shopify theme and im having a weird issue with the product template. on desktop it looks fine but when i check it on my phone the product image is totally overlapping the title and description. cant tell if its a padding issue or something with the media queries. \n\nhere is the css for the product section:\n\n.product-container {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: row;\n  gap: 20px;\n}\n\n.product-media {\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n.product-info {\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {\n  .product-container {\n    display: block;\n  }\n  .product-media, .product-info {\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n}\n\nthe liquid looks standard too. can u see what might be causing the overlap?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it seems like your product image and text are trying to be more than they can be, causing them to overlap. In the desktop version, they are living their best lives in a flex container, but when it comes to mobile, they are trying to fit into a block container, which isn't quite right.\n\nI suspect the issue is that the product image and product info are both trying to take up 100% of the width when they're in the block container. This is causing them to overlap because they're both trying to fit into the same space.\n\nTo fix this, you could try changing the flex direction to column in the media query for mobile. This way, the product image and product info will stack on top of each other instead of trying to fit side by side. Here's what the updated media query would look like:\n\n@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {\n  .product-container {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n  }\n  .product-media, .product-info {\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n}\n\nThis should fix the overlap issue on mobile. Let me know if you have any other questions or if there's anything else I can help you with!",
      "source": "target",
