      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks that worked for that specific section. but now that they are stacked, i'm seeing some weird spacing issues. there's like this massive gap between the image and the title on mobile, but on desktop it looks perfectly fine. it feels like something is pushing them apart way too much on the small screens. i tried adding a margin-bottom to the media, but it didnt really change anything. any idea why the spacing would behave so inconsistently like that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the spacing issue is a classic case of the mobile vs. desktop divide. On desktop, your product image and title are living side by side in harmony, but on mobile, they're trying to be best friends in a single row, and it's causing them to drift apart.\n\nOne possible reason for the inconsistent spacing could be the default margin and padding applied by the browser on mobile devices. Sometimes, these default styles can cause unexpected gaps between elements, especially when you're trying to stack them.\n\nTo address this, you could try adding a margin-top to the product-media and a margin-bottom to the product-info in the media query. This should help to reduce the gap between the image and the title on mobile. Here's an updated version of your media query:\n\n@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {\n  .product-container {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n  }\n  .product-media, .product-info {\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n  .product-media {\n    margin-top: 10px; /* Adjust this value as needed */\n  }\n  .product-info {\n    margin-bottom: 10px; /* Adjust this value as needed */\n  }\n}\n\nTry adjusting the margin values",
      "source": "target",
